{
  "claim_boundary": "cuNxon GPU execution has runtime/dynamics viability and exposes snapshot/pattern/multi-sphere/interface APIs from Python, but most task-coupled probes remain diagnostic/negative: pattern recall readouts are flat zero, the multi-sphere action adapter decodes all cases to query, a 108-sample long sweep matches constant-action baselines at 0.333333 accuracy, the supervised motor-target adapter stays at constant-query baseline accuracy, and the resident action probe also stays at baseline accuracy across every epoch. The interface semantics probe supports absolute neuron-index readout mapping, while the source semantics audit found no desired-output API surface and explains why teacher-forcing absolute output-neuron target ports through sensory inputs is unsupported by the kernel path. The input-proxy and external-drive probes confirm that supported input-class drive is observable but not a motor target channel. The four-hour VRAM-resident run adds process-residence/runtime evidence, not decision-quality evidence. The Aigarth readout/action route remains the only constructive action-quality lead so far: target-contract fitness moved the signed-first-lane decoder contract into train-only Aigarth optimization and removed unexpected labels. The stress audit exposed baseline-level low-margin stress_holdout behavior, and the augmented-train follow-up improved hard_holdout/holdout while stress_holdout stayed at 0.333333 and counterfactual_control stayed non-zero at 0.066667. This is useful objective-shaping/brittleness evidence, not broad intelligence/generalization evidence. Qubic NIA Vol. 8 adds branching ratio/criticality as an explicit regime-diagnostic hypothesis, but the new claim map treats it as necessary instrumentation rather than intelligence evidence unless it predicts held-out task quality above baselines.",
